SIMPLE: meanness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meanness
<hw>Mean"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition, or
quality, of being mean; want of excellence; poorness; lowness; baseness;
sordidness; stinginess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This figure is of a later date, by the <qex>meanness</qex> of the
workmanship.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mean act; <as>as, to be guilty of
<ex>meanness</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mean-spirited</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>meanspirited</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>
